# 🚀 Free-Tier Deployment & Multi-Tenant RAG Architecture Plan

This document outlines a thorough analysis of the FastAPI-LangGraph Chatbot codebase, identifies all paid or deployment-restricting components, provides a curated 100% free-tier replacement list using **Google Gemini**, **MongoDB**, and **Qdrant Cloud**, and explains how to implement a fully secured, multi-tenant RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) system.

---

## 🔍 Detailed Codebase & Deployment Analysis

To deploy your unified chatbot frontend and backend as a **single consolidated server on Render (Free Tier)**, we must address several severe limitations and configuration requirements:

1. **Ephemeral File System (Render Free Tier):**
   * **The Issue:** The backend currently uses SQLite (`sqlite:///./app.db`). Under Render's free tier, standard disks are ephemeral. Every time the server sleeps due to 15 minutes of inactivity, or redeploys, your entire database (registered users, tenant settings, and chat relations) will be deleted.
   * **Vector Store Client:** Standard Qdrant runs locally (`localhost:6333`). This is impossible to maintain on Render without paying for a dedicated Docker instance or persistent storage.
2. **WebRTC & Network Restrictions (Render Free Tier):**
   * **The Issue:** The `livekit_agent.py` establishes a persistent WebRTC agent connection using PyTorch (Silero VAD) and third-party WebRTC channels. Render free-tier services only expose single HTTP ports (80/443). They do not support custom UDP/TCP routing required for WebRTC. Furthermore, PyTorch-based VAD consumes >512MB RAM, causing the Render container to crash with Out-Of-Memory (OOM) errors.
3. **High Operational Costs (Paid APIs):**
   * **The Issue:** The current codebase is heavily locked into **OpenAI (GPT-4o-mini & Text-Embedding-3-small)**, **Tavily (Search)**, **Firecrawl (Scraping)**, **Deepgram (STT)**, and **Cartesia (TTS)**. These require paid subscriptions or have extremely restrictive trial limits.

---

## 📋 The 100% Free-Tier Replacement List

Here is the exact replacement matrix that guarantees **100% free operation**, high performance, and smooth, single-server Render compatibility:

| Current Component | Free-Tier Replacement | Description & Free Limits |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **LLM Orchestration** | **Google Gemini 2.5 Flash / 1.5 Flash** (via Google AI Studio) | Extremely generous free tier: **15 RPM / 1,500 RPD / 1M TPM**. State-of-the-art reasoning and large context window. |
| **Embeddings** | **Gemini Embeddings (`text-embedding-004`)** | Fully free to generate high-quality 768-dimension vector embeddings using your Google AI Studio API key. |
| **Vector Store** | **Qdrant Cloud Free Tier** | Provides **1 free cluster** (1GB RAM, 0.5 CPU, up to 4M vectors) which is fully persistent and cloud-hosted. |
| **Main Database & Chat Sessions** | **MongoDB Atlas M0 Free Tier** | Cloud-hosted MongoDB offering **512 MB of persistent storage** forever. Perfect for users, tenants, and sessions. |
| **Web Search Tool** | **DuckDuckGo Search** (via LangChain Community) | **100% free**, no signup required, no rate limit issues for general search tasks. |
| **Web Scraper Tool** | **BeautifulSoup4 + HTTP Client** (Custom tool) | Runs directly in the Render container for **unlimited free scraping** of public webpages. |
| **Voice Mode (STT/TTS)** | **Client-Side Web Speech API** (STT/TTS in Browser) | Implemented directly in React. Offloads **100%** of audio processing, speech-to-text, and text-to-speech to the browser engine. Zero server load. |
| **Session Memory** | **Open-source Mem0 library configured with Google Gemini API** | Uses the free `mem0ai` library configured with Gemini 1.5 Flash (LLM) and `text-embedding-004` (Embedder) connecting to your free Qdrant Cloud. |

---

## 🏗️ Adding the Multi-Tenant RAG Architecture

To implement a secure, multi-tenant RAG (Document QA) system, we will:
1. Allow users to upload a comprehensive set of documents, media, and data formats via the React frontend:
   * **Documents:** PDF (`.pdf`), Word Document (`.docx`), Old Word (`.doc`), Markdown (`.md`), Plain Text (`.txt`)
   * **Structured Data:** CSV (`.csv`), Excel (`.xlsx`), Old Excel (`.xls`), JSON (`.json`), XML (`.xml`)
   * **Presentations:** PowerPoint (`.pptx`), Old PowerPoint (`.ppt`)
   * **Web & Scraping:** HTML (`.html`), Web URLs (web scraping)
   * **Images (OCR):** PNG (`.png`), JPG/JPEG (`.jpg`, `.jpeg`) for text extraction
   * **Audio (Transcripts):** MP3, WAV, etc., processed via speech models (Whisper/Client STT)
   * **Archives:** Compressed directories (`.zip`) containing any of the supported formats
2. Store files securely, extract text, and segment it into manageable chunks.
3. Embed chunks with tenant isolation (`tenant_id` and `user_id` payload filters) and store them in the Qdrant Cloud vector database.
4. Retrieve relevant contexts on-demand using payload filters during the LangGraph execution flow.

### 🔄 Multi-Tenant RAG Data Flow (Ingestion & Retrieval)

This sequence diagram outlines the isolated data paths for both document ingestion (Phase 1) and secure context-stuffed query execution (Phase 2):

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User App (React)
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant Gemini as Gemini API (AI Studio)
    participant Qdrant as Qdrant Cloud (Free Tier)
    participant DB as MongoDB Atlas

    note over User, DB: PHASE 1: DOCUMENT INGESTION FLOW (RAG)
    User->>API: Upload File (PDF/DOCX/TXT/CSV/XLSX/PPTX/HTML/MD/JSON/Images/Audio/Zip) + JWT Token
    API->>API: JWT Middleware extracts tenant_id & user_id
    API->>API: Extract raw text content (PdfReader / UTF-8)
    API->>API: Split content into chunks (1000 chars, 200 overlap)
    API->>Gemini: Request Embeddings for chunks (text-embedding-004)
    Gemini-->>API: Return 768-dimension vectors
    API->>Qdrant: Store vectors with metadata (tenant_id, user_id, filename)
    Qdrant-->>API: Confirm storage (payload filtered collection)
    API-->>User: Ingestion Completed successfully (200 OK)

    note over User, DB: PHASE 2: CHAT & CONTEXT-AWARE RETRIEVAL FLOW
    User->>API: Ask Question ("Based on my documents...") + JWT
    API->>API: JWT Middleware extracts tenant_id & user_id
    API->>Gemini: Request Embedding for Query (text-embedding-004)
    Gemini-->>API: Return query vector
    API->>Qdrant: Query vector with strict Payload Filter (tenant_id & user_id)
    Qdrant-->>API: Return top K isolated relevant document chunks
    API->>API: Stuff document chunks into LangGraph System Prompt
    API->>API: Load cross-chat context from Mem0 Memory
    API->>Gemini: Invoke LLM with complete context (Gemini 1.5 Flash)
    Gemini-->>API: Stream completion tokens
    API->>DB: Persist conversation history & session state
    API-->>User: Stream final response via SSE (text/event-stream)
```

